             <div class="txtNew" data-packed="true" id="comp-jif60y3q" style="top:676px;bottom:;left:673px;right:;width:278px;height:auto;position:absolute;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">

             <div class="hl2" id="comp-jg5ph22y" style="top:757px;bottom:;left:667px;right:;width:284px;height:5px;position:absolute;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <div class="hl2line" id="comp-jg5ph22yline">
              </div>
             </div>
             <style data-styleid="hl2" type="text/css">
              .hl2 {border-bottom:1px solid rgba(112, 91, 67, 1);height:0 !important;min-height:0 !important;}

             <div class="txtNew" data-min-height="575" data-packed="false" id="comp-jg5p8cfe" style="top:766px;bottom:;left:659px;right:;width:300px;height:auto;position:absolute;min-height:575px;margin-left:calc((100% - 980px) * 0.5)">
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                  Line &amp; Color:
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-weight:bold;">
                 <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                  The Nature of Ellsworth Kelly
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                 June 1, 2018 - Ocotber 29,2018
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-family:caudex,serif;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-family:caudex,serif;">
                 In 1948, artist Ellsworth Kelly moved to Paris in order to be near all that European culture had to offer. He stayed for almost a decade, traveling to see museums and making sketches of frescoes and stone sculptures in the many cities he visited, something he was not able to do while he was stationed near Paris during World War II. He befriended fellow American artists while absorbing the artwork of the early 20th century, as well as European masters such as Arp, Matisse and Brancusi. In the mid-1950s, he moved back to the United States just as New York was becoming a central cultural hub. By this point, Kellys creative vocabulary had been established. His vision of abstraction reflected the world around him, rather than the emotional and process-based abstraction of New York artists such as Pollock, Rothko and de Kooning.
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-family:caudex,serif;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px; text-align:center;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                 For more Information:
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="text-decoration:underline;">
                 <a data-content="https://www.nortonsimon.org/exhibitions/2010-2019/line-and-color-the-nature-of-ellsworth-kelly/" data-type="external" href="https://www.nortonsimon.org/exhibitions/2010-2019/line-and-color-the-nature-of-ellsworth-kelly/" rel="undefined" target="_blank">
                  <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                   https://www.nortonsimon.org/exhibitions/2010-2019/line-and-color-the-nature-of-ellsworth-kelly/
                  </span>
                 </a>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>
              <p class="font_8" style="font-size:15px;">
               <span style="font-size:15px;">
                <span style="font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif;">
                 <span class="wixGuard">
                  
                 </span>
                </span>
               </span>
              </p>

text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif\">Line &amp; Color: <\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif\">The Nature of Ellsworth Kelly<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif\">June 1, 2018 - Ocotber 29,2018<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:caudex,serif\"><span class=\"wixGuard\"><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:caudex,serif\">In 1948, artist Ellsworth Kelly moved to Paris in order to be near all that European culture had to offer. He stayed for almost a decade, traveling to see museums and making sketches of frescoes and stone sculptures in the many cities he visited, something he was not able to do while he was stationed near Paris during World War II. He befriended fellow American artists while absorbing the artwork of the early 20th century, as well as European masters such as Arp, Matisse and Brancusi. In the mid-1950s, he moved back to the United States just as New York was becoming a central cultural hub. By this point, Kelly&rsquo;s creative vocabulary had been established. His vision of abstraction reflected the world around him, rather than the emotional and process-based abstraction of New York artists such as Pollock, Rothko and de Kooning.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:caudex,serif\"><span class=\"wixGuard\"><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-weight:bold\"><span style=\"font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif\">The Nature of Ellsworth Kelly<\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:futura-lt-w01-book,sans-serif\">June 1, 2018 - Ocotber 29,2018<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px; text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:caudex,serif\"><span class=\"wixGuard\"><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:caudex,serif\">In 1948, artist Ellsworth Kelly moved to Paris in order to be near all that European culture had to offer. He stayed for almost a decade, traveling to see museums and making sketches of frescoes and stone sculptures in the many cities he visited, something he was not able to do while he was stationed near Paris during World War II. He befriended fellow American artists while absorbing the artwork of the early 20th century, as well as European masters such as Arp, Matisse and Brancusi. In the mid-1950s, he moved back to the United States just as New York was becoming a central cultural hub. By this point, Kelly&rsquo;s creative vocabulary had been established. His vision of abstraction reflected the world around him, rather than the emotional and process-based abstraction of New York artists such as Pollock, Rothko and de Kooning.<\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-size:15px\"><span style=\"font-family:caudex,serif\"><span class=\"wixGuard\"><\/span><\/span><\/span><\/p>\n\n<p class=\"font_8\" style=\"font-size:15px;
